records.addlTxt:
Defendant Brendan J Washington in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of State, Court ordered count dismissed.

AS TO COUNT 1: Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence with credit for 7 days time served; STRAIGHT TIME.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS. 
Conditions:  
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Possess no weapons;
*  Perform 10 hours of community service;
*  Pay all costs and sucharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
